import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    terrain_count = data.groupby('name').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='name', y='count', data=terrain_count)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of terrain types?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='y', y='lumosity', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between terrain height and brightness?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.lineplot(x='x', y='id', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of terrain creation timestamps?', wrap=True)
